description:
The «СОЮЗСНАБ» Group of Companies offers confectionery glaze under the "KLASSIKA" trademark from the manufacturing company "Green Lines," based on lauric-type cocoa butter substitutes. Triglycerides containing lauric acid possess important properties for glazed products:
• sharply defined melting point;
• short melting and solidification period;
• low viscosity in a molten state.
Glazes made from various lauric fats are presented in a wide assortment. Depending on the client's wishes, we can offer options with different properties. For example, glaze with high hardness, good gloss, and brittleness, and reduced setting time. For those who prefer a softer consistency, we offer a glaze that provides a pliable coating and strong adhesion to the glazed surface upon solidification.

Common Composition: Sugar, non-tempered lauric-type cocoa butter substitute (hydrogenated fractionated refined palm kernel oil, emulsifiers (soy lecithin, E492)), cocoa powder, skimmed milk powder, refined deodorized coconut oil, cocoa mass, whole milk powder, dry whey, emulsifiers (soy lecithin, E492, E 476), "Vanilla" flavoring, "Vanillin" flavor substance.

